One of the best solution to avoid memory leak is to avoid polluting the global variable scope.
You can place your data inside function, the garbage collector will clean the variable after the function is invoked, you can use IIFE for example:

    (function fnWrapper() {
      var data = &#39;This is huge data&#39;;
      console.log(data);
    })();

The var data will be deleted from the memory heap after your code runs. (except if it has been used inside nested functions or what they might call &quot;Closure&quot;) 
